                          Quick Summary

You may copy, distribute and modify the software as long as you track 
changes/dates in source files. Any modifications to or software 
including (via compiler) GPL-licensed code must also be made 
available under the GPL along with build & install instructions.

A one using this program ( as well as any portion of that) should: 

1. Include Original:
  The copies of the original software, mention of the license file 
  (and therefore the source code) location (the github repository of the software url) or 
  instructions to obtain copies should be distributed with software using the provided library or code under the current license, Or:
2. Include License:
  Including the full text of license in modified software (in case condition in paragraph 1. was not fulfilled).
3. State Changes:
  All code linked with GPL 3.0 source code should be disclosed under a GPL 3.0 compatible license.
4. Include Copyright:
  The original copyright should be retained.
5. Include Install Instructions:
  If the software is part of a consumer device, the one using the software 
  should include the installation information necessary to modify and reinstall the software.

